"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427331","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-10","<p>The Government recognises the importance of sustaining a vibrant research community across the UK. A key criterion for allocating the £4.6billion per year of research funding is “maintaining a substantial flow of new researchers and high level skills”. Research Councils support 10,000 researchers many of whom are in early research careers, as well as Doctoral Training Centres. National Academies also support early-career researchers with the potential to become leaders in their chosen fields.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-11-10T15:38:26.807Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427331/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427331/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427331/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-04","Research: Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will take steps to ensure that funding is available to maintain work opportunities for researchers in the early stages of their careers.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart McDonald","902104"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427332","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-10","<p>We will establish a Small Business Commissioner to help small businesses deal with late payment disputes. We are also introducing new payment reporting requirements for large companies that will allow public scrutiny of payment performance</p><br /><p>I was pleased to see Tesco has cut its payment terms to 14 days for suppliers with total sales to Tesco worth less than £100,000 a year.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-11-10T15:33:38.07Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427332/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427332/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427332/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-04","Small Businesses: Billing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he is taking to encourage prompt payment to small businesses.","false","Biography information for Marion Fellows","Motherwell and Wishaw","Marion Fellows","902101"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427333","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-10","<p>From my visits to Scunthorpe, Redcar, Port Talbot and Cardiff, I know first-hand what a dedicated and skilled workforce exists in the industry and am determined that they have a future, with the action the government has taken and will continue to take to help the industry.</p><br /><p>For those workers that have unfortunately lost their jobs, the government is committed to doing all we can to give them the support and training needed to quickly return to work. We have made available up to £80 million for Redcar and announced up to £9 million for Scunthorpe to support those who have been affected.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-11-10T15:35:16.64Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427333/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427333/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427333/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-04","Iron and Steel: Skilled Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he is taking to ensure that the skills of steel industry employees are maintained.","false","Biography information for Valerie  Vaz","Walsall South","Valerie Vaz","902100"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427334","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-10","<p>As at 30 June, the North East accounts for 5% of the finance facilitated by the British Business Bank. Given that the North East accounts for 3% of the small business population this means that the region enjoys more than its pro rata share of Business Bank investment.</p><br /><p>I am pleased that since 2010, there are 11,800 new businesses in the North East. The historic Tees Valley devolution deal, worth £450million, and the North East Combined Authority deal, worth £900million, recently signed by the Chancellor will help drive locally led economic growth and a thriving business environment.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-11-10T15:37:05.763Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427334/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427334/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427334/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-04","Small Businesses: North East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what proportion of investments made through the British Business Bank has been made in the North East.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","902102"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427335","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-10","<p>The Government is determined to encourage more consumers to vote with their feet in key markets like energy, banking and telecoms. We are currently conducting a Call for Evidence on a set of six “switching principles”. Once fully implemented, these will make the process quicker and easier for consumers.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-11-10T15:32:20.217Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427335/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427335/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/427335/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-04","Utilities: Competition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he is taking to encourage competition and switching between providers in consumer markets.","false","Biography information for Nigel Huddleston","Mid Worcestershire","Nigel Huddleston","902105"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425595","Attorney General","false","2015-11-10","<p>I refer my Hon. Friend to my Answer of 17 September 2015. Work is on-going on the possible application to the court for directions on the future of the National Fund, consistent with its object of extinguishing or reducing the national debt. I am also continuing to consider other options. I will update my Hon. Friend as soon as I can.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2015-11-10T12:18:01.427Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425595/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425595/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425595/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2015-11-03","National Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, pursuant to the Answer of 17 September 2015 to Question 10237, when he expects to publish proposals for the future of the National Debt Fund.","false","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","14565"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425596","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-06","<p>It is not part of the Secretary of State’s functions to assess the performance of the Official Receiver when acting as liquidator. The Secretary of State cannot interfere in the administration of the liquidation.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-11-06T14:17:40.803Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425596/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425596/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425596/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-03","Sahaviriya Steel Industries UK: Redcar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will assess the performance of the Official Receiver during the liquidation of SSI UK.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","14661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425597","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-13","<br /><p>There are a number of different elements of support for people affected by the closure of the SSI steelworks in Redcar. These include:</p><br /><ul><li>Redundancy-related payments paid by the Redundancy Payments Service. 1988 payments are currently being or have been processed and the majority of payments made to individuals.</li></ul><br /><ul><li>A Jobs Fair, which was attended by over 1800 people</li></ul><br /><ul><li>A Jobcentre Plus helpline, which has dealt with around 4000 calls</li></ul><br /><ul><li>A support Hub, which has provided a wide range of advice and guidance to over 2000 individuals</li></ul><p>The Government will not impose solutions from Whitehall and will continue to work closely with the local taskforce to deliver the proposals it has identified as having a real and lasting impact. This includes:</p><br /><p>- a £1.7m support fund to enable SSI’s 50 apprentices complete their training</p><br /><p>- a £16.5m Jobs and Skills Fund to help local firms employ former SSI workers or their spouses in full-time or part-time jobs for a minimum of three years</p><br /><p>- £16m support for firms in the SSI supply chain and wider Tees Valley impacted by the Redcar steelworks closure, to safeguard jobs, provide the stimulus to create new posts and provide expert assistance to help them expand their business</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-11-13T14:14:48.583Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425597/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425597/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425597/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-03","Sahaviriya Steel Industries UK: Redcar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate he has made of the number of people who have accessed the Government support package for people affected by the closure of the SSI steelworks in Redcar.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","14662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425598","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-06","<p>The package, worth up to £80 million, announced to support former SSI workers and the Tees Valley economy more broadly was agreed across Government.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-11-06T14:20:25.88Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425598/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425598/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425598/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-03","Sahaviriya Steel Industries UK: Redcar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what discussions he has had with the Prime Minister about the value of the Government support package for people affected by the closure of the SSI Steelworks in Redcar.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","14663"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425599","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-22","<p>The package, worth up to £80 million, announced to support former SSI workers and the Tees Valley economy more broadly was based on an initial assessment of what could make an immediate and lasting difference to the people affected and the local economy.</p><br /><p>We are looking closely Task Force to deliver proposals which they have identified will help recover from this closure, including funding to support apprentices complete their training, support for workers to retrain, and help for local businesses to grow. As the Prime Minister and Secretary of State have said, should more funding be needed, we will consider that.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-12-22T15:12:53.507Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425599/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425599/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425599/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-03","Sahaviriya Steel Industries UK: Redcar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what criteria were used to cap the value of the Government support package to £80 million for people affected by the closure of SSI Redcar.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","14664"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425600","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-02","<p>UK Trade and Investment’s (UKTI) mining sector team has regular and ongoing engagement with Rio Tinto both in market and in the UK as we seek to realise economic benefit for the UK through the involvement of the UK’s mining supply chain in Rio Tinto’s projects.</p><p>Rio Tinto closed its Lynemouth Aluminium facility in 2013. That same year UKTI was part of a Rapid Response taskforce (which included local Economic Development organisations and Rio Tinto), to explore redeployment and site re-marketing options.</p><p>UKTI support included:</p><p>- an audit of the unique characteristics and selling points of the site to determine the sectoral focus of Rio Tinto’s site marketing activity to potential investors.</p><p>- research to assess from where the strongest investor interest was likely to come from.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","14507","2015-12-02T09:50:31.143Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425600/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425600/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425600/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-03","Rio Tinto Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what support UKTI has provided to Rio Tinto in locations where Rio Tinto invests or plans to invest.","false","Biography information for Ian Lavery","Wansbeck","Ian Lavery","14508"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425601","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-11","<p>The Government recognises the importance of sustaining a strong research community across the UK. In allocating Science and Research funding, the Government asks the Research Councils, Higher Education Funding Council for England, British Academy, Royal Academy of Engineering and Royal Society to ensure that they are “maintaining a substantial flow of new researchers and high level skills”. Research Councils support 14,000 research staff and fellows, including 10,000 university researchers, many of whom are in early research careers. The National Academies provide over 690 early career research fellowships.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-11-11T17:10:22.8Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425601/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425601/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425601/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-03","Higher Education: Research","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what support his Department is providing to higher education institutions to increase the number of post-doctoral positions offered; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","14549"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425602","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-09","<p>The Department encourages more responsible supply chain management by businesses, including retailers, by requiring companies to be more transparent about their business operations. UK listed companies are required to report on social and environmental matters where necessary for an understanding of their business.</p><p>More widely, the Government supports the Ethical Trading Initiative which helps member companies realise their commitment to continuous improvement in ethical sourcing.</p><p>We are also providing £18 million over six years to help Fairtrade International have a greater impact in their work and strengthen the global Fairtrade system.</p><p>The Government also supports work by the Waste and Resources Action Programme (WRAP) on voluntary agreements such as the Sustainable Clothing Action Plan which encourages sustainability of clothing across the product life cycle including, for example, use of lower impact fibres. In addition, Government co-ordinates work on the UK statement on the sustainable production of palm oil, working with retailers and others towards achieving 100% sourcing of credibly certified sustainable palm oil in the UK.</p><p>In October the transparency in supply chains provision (section 54) of the Modern Slavery Act came into force.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-11-09T15:01:40.183Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425602/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425602/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425602/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-03","Retail Trade: Sustainable Development","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps his Department is taking to encourage retailers to source their products from ethical and sustainable sources; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","14532"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425603","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-09","<p>The Government does not have a policy of the kind described in this question. Our policy on the House of Lords is described in the Conservative Party election manifesto 2015.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2015-11-09T16:46:19.767Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425603/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425603/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425603/answer","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425603/answer/previousversion/28335","Biography information for John Penrose","53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-03","House of Lords Composition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether it is the Government's policy to increase the membership of the House of Lords by over 100 members during the course of this Parliament.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","14479"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425604","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-11-10","<p>As announced by the Prime Minister in Written StatementHCWS278 on 29 October 2015, policy responsibility for digital inclusion transferred from the Cabinet Office to the Department for Culture, Media and Sport on 1 November 2015.</p><p>Government is already investing in world class infrastructure (e.g. in the form of superfast broadband coverage) but access alone isn’t enough - people need the skills to benefit from online. The most recent funding figures available are £0.12m in 2013/14 and £0.30m in 2014/15. Our Digital Inclusion Strategy, published in April 2014, sets out how we plan to increase the level of digital engagement across the UK. Significantprogress in this area is already being made by public, private and voluntary sector organisations - dozens of which have signed up to the Digital Inclusion Charter.You can find more information on the Charter here:<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/government-digital-inclusion-strategy/uk-digital-inclusion-charter" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/government-digital-inclusion-strategy/uk-digital-inclusion-charter</a></p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-11-10T16:23:37.733Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425604/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425604/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425604/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-11-03","Cabinet Office: Digital Technology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the funding was for the Digital Inclusion team in his Department in each year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","14620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425605","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-06","<p>The Data Steering Group has been established, chaired by the National Statistician, John Pullinger, which brings together leading experts to advise government on the strategic direction of the new Government Data Programme. Notes of these meetings will be made available on the Government Data Programme blog page on GOV.UK in due course.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","14621","2015-11-06T13:25:41.573Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425605/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425605/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425605/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-03","Cabinet Office: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 15 October 2015 to Question 11489, when the Chief Data Officer will be appointed.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","14622"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425606","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-06","<p>The Data Steering Group has been established, chaired by the National Statistician, John Pullinger, which brings together leading experts to advise government on the strategic direction of the new Government Data Programme. Notes of these meetings will be made available on the Government Data Programme blog page on GOV.UK in due course.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","14622","2015-11-06T13:25:41.507Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425606/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425606/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425606/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-03","Cabinet Office: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 15 October 2015 to Question 11489, if he will make available the minutes of the Data Steering Group.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","14621"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425607","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-09","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2015-11-09T11:01:33.49Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425607/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425607/answer","09112015 PQ14567.pdf","09112015 PQ14567.pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Suicide Rate","UKSA Letter to Member - Suicide Rate","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425607/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-03","Suicide: Males","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the suicide rate was for young men in (a) Barnsley Central constituency, (b) Yorkshire and the Humber and (c) the UK in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","14567"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425608","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-11","<p>The information requested can be obtained from “National Infrastructure Pipeline”, published in July 2015 and is available here:</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-infrastructure-pipeline-july-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-infrastructure-pipeline-july-2015</a></p><br />","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-11-11T11:54:38.52Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425608/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425608/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425608/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-03","Infrastructure: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much is expected to be allocated to Northern Ireland under the National Infrastructure pipeline in each of the next five years.","false","Biography information for Dr Alasdair McDonnell","Belfast South","Dr Alasdair McDonnell","14574"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425609","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-06","<p>The current account deficit in 2014 was 5.1% of GDP, with this net borrowing from the rest of the world helping fund the budget deficit. The Government’s plan to repair the public finances through fiscal consolidation should in turn improve the current account deficit, as set out in the latest forecasts of the Office for Budget Responsibility.</p><br /><p>The Government is also working to boost UK exports, including a £20m package of support for first time exporters and working alongside a more effective UKTI and better export finance.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-11-06T13:55:47.073Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425609/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425609/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425609/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-03","Balance of Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of the size of the current account balance in 2014.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","14589"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425610","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-06","<p>The Office for Budget Responsibility, which provides independent forecast for the Government, does not produce a forecast for manufacturing output.</p><br /><p>Manufacturing has grown 4.1% from the start of 2010, following a 12.5% fall in the financial crisis. The headline manufacturing PMI accelerated to 55.5 in October, recording its fastest expansion rate in two and a half years.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-11-06T13:30:41.873Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425610/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425610/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425610/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-03","Manufacturing Industries","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he expects manufacturing output to exceed the level of quarter one in 2008.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","14590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425611","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-11","<p>I refer the Honourable Gentleman to the answer the Financial Secretary to the Treasury, my hon. Friend, the Member for South West Hertfordshire (David Gauke MP), gave on 16 October 2015 (PQ10437, PQ10438 and PQ10448), which sets out the criteria we expect the Overseas Territories to meet in relation to their central register of company beneficial ownership, or similarly effective system.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2015-11-11T14:33:06.33Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425611/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425611/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425611/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-11-03","Companies: Ownership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will ensure that any agreement on a central registry of beneficial ownership in the British Virgin Islands will include access for the public with legitimate reason, in line with the Fourth EU Anti Money Laundering Directive.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","14573"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425612","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-11","<p>As announced at the Summer Budget, we have asked the Department for Transport to look at extending the Mersey Gateway local discount scheme to residents of Chester West &amp; Chester and Warrington, as well as looking at help for small businesses. This work is ongoing.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","14501 ; 14502","2015-11-11T11:52:20.523Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425612/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425612/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425612/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-03","Mersey Gateway Project","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he expects there to be an announcement on the extension of the Mersey Gateway free travel scheme to residents and businesses in Cheshire; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir George Howarth","Knowsley","Mr George Howarth","14554"
