"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425632","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-18","<p>The National Minimum Wage rate structure provides different rates according to age and the National Living Wage will apply to those aged 25 and over. The Low Pay Commission will continue to monitor, evaluate and review pay conditions for younger workers when it makes recommendations for future changes to the National Minimum Wage and National Living Wage.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-11-18T12:49:07.433Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425632/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425632/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425632/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-03","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate he has made of the likely change in the pay gap between workers under and over 25 and those older than 25 over the course of the 2015 Parliament.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","14535"
