"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425792","Department of Health","false","2015-11-10","<p>Some NHS Help with Health Costs claim forms, for example HC5 refund claim forms, have been amended to include a specific tick box to enable Universal Credit recipients to claim entitlement.</p><br /><p>Form HC1 (NHS Low Income Scheme application form) has been amended to include a sentence about Universal Credit, to advise those applying that until 31 October 2015, anyone in receipt of Universal Credit does not need to complete the form, as they will already be entitled to Help with Health Costs.</p><br /><p>Other forms, including: NHS prescription forms (FP10); dental treatment claim forms (FP17) and claims for NHS funded sight tests (GOS 1) and for vouchers for glasses or contact lenses (GOS 3) will be amended to include a Universal Credit box in due course.</p><br /><p>A patient can make a claim for entitlement by ticking the “gets income based Jobseekers Allowance” on relevant forms. Guidance for both the public and healthcare practitioners (such as pharmacists, dentist and opticians) has been included on NHS Choices with links from the Universal Credit webpages on Gov.uk.</p><br />","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-11-10T15:59:54.32Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425792/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425792/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425792/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-03","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 16 October 2015 to Question 11786 and the Answer of 12 October 2015 to Question 10360, on universal credit, whether a box for universal credit exists on NHS charges claim forms.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","14672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425793","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-06","<p>The Department does not make any direct payments to libraries in relation to partnering on the delivery of digital inclusion.</p><p>DWP is working with Local Authorities through ‘Universal Support’ to build claimants’ digital capability. Libraries are one potential route for delivering this support, where deemed appropriate by our Local Authority partners.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-11-06T14:18:50.25Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425793/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425793/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425793/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-03","Department for Work and Pensions: Digital Technology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 28 October 2015 to Question 13246, what payment is given to libraries to partner with the Department on digital inclusion.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","14668"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425794","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-06","<p>Those people without digital skills will be offered support through Universal Credit (UC) to make and manage their claims on-line, and also to acquire and improve their digital skills.</p><p>DWP is also working with Local Authorities to build claimants’ digital capability.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-11-06T14:07:51.033Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425794/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425794/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425794/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-03","Department for Work and Pensions: Digital Technology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 28 October 2015 to Question 13246 on digital technology, what support universal credit provides for people without digital skills to gain them.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","14669"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425795","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-11-06","<p>Under powers in the Coroners Act 1988 (as amended) a new coroner investigation may be ordered by the High Court, with the authority of the Attorney General, where it is in the interests of justice to do so because of fraud, rejection of evidence, irregularity of proceedings or insufficiency of inquiry in the original inquest or new facts or evidence have come to light. It therefore falls outside the responsibility of the Secretary of State.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2015-11-06T10:53:30.133Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425795/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425795/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425795/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-11-03","Stephen O'Malley","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will make representations to his Danish counterpart on reopening the inquest into the death of commercial diver Stephen O'Malley in 2012.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Mrs Louise Ellman","14660"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425796","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-09","<p>Information on the number of claims to Personal Independence Payment (PIP) by war veterans is not available as details about current or previous occupations are not collected as part of the application or assessment process.</p><p>Service personnel and veterans who are entitled to a Guaranteed Income Payment of 50% or higher through the Armed Forces Compensation Scheme are eligible to apply for Armed Forces Independence Payment instead of PIP. There have been 873 applications for this payment to date.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-11-09T14:49:36.977Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425796/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425796/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425796/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-03","Personal Independence Payment: Veterans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many war veterans have applied for personal independence payment.","false","Biography information for Owen Smith","Pontypridd","Owen Smith","14529"
