"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425248","Leader of the House of Lords","false","2015-11-16","<p>Statistics compiled by the Journal Office indicate that the percentage of House of Lords divisions resulting in Government defeats were as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Parliament</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Percentage of defeats</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2001-05</p></td><td><p>38%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2005-10</p></td><td><p>32%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-15</p></td><td><p>21%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-</p></td><td><p>69%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong><br></strong></p>",,"Baroness Stowell of Beeston",,"2015-11-16T16:42:51.81Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425248/answer","Biography information for Baroness Stowell of Beeston","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425248/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425248/answer",,,,,"92",,"Leader of the House of Lords","2015-11-02","House of Lords: Government Defeats","2","House of Lords","To ask the Leader of the House what percentage of House of Lords divisions resulted in Government defeats (1) in the 2001–2005 Parliament; (2) in the 2005–2010 Parliament; (3) in the 2010–2015 Parliament; and (4) since the 2015 general election to date.","false","Biography information for Lord Dobbs",,"Lord Dobbs","HL3174"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425249","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-11","<p>The Government has a number of ongoing projects to investigate issues surrounding solid wall insulation, including monitoring current installation practices (DECC), modelling the risks of unintended moisture-related problems (DCLG and DECC), preparing practical guidance for industry to reduce the risks of such problems (DECC) and a wider high-level study of solid wall insulation issues (BIS – the Hansford report, to be published on 12 November).</p><br /><p>The Government recognises that it is important that we do more and that is why we have commissioned Dr Peter Bonfield to undertake an Independent Review into Consumer Advice, Protection, Standards and Enforcement for both energy efficiency and renewable energy. The Review is due to report in March 2016 and represents a real opportunity to put energy efficiency on a more consumer-focussed and sustainable long-term path for the future.</p><br />",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2015-11-11T13:03:51.177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425249/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425249/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425249/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-02","Housing: Insulation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the difficulties associated with the insulation of external walls of traditional terraced housing and other older properties with solid walls rather than cavity walls, and whether they are supporting, or will support, research into practical solutions for insulating such walls.","false","Biography information for Lord Greaves",,"Lord Greaves","HL3175"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425250","Home Office","false","2015-11-12","<p>The numbers of Iraqi nationals (main applicants and dependants) granted asylum or another form of protection in the UK, in each year since 2010 were as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="6"><strong>Number of Iraqi nationals granted asylum or another form of protection in the UK (for main applicants and dependants), based on initial decisions<sup>1</sup> </strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Year</strong></td><td><strong>Total grants<sup>2 </sup></strong></td></tr><tr><td>2010</td><td>169</td></tr><tr><td>2011</td><td>113</td></tr><tr><td>2012</td><td>95</td></tr><tr><td>2013</td><td>109</td></tr><tr><td>2014</td><td>208</td></tr><tr><td colspan="6">(1) Initial decisions do not necessarily relate to applications made in the same period and exclude the outcome of appeals or other subsequent decisions.</td></tr><tr><td colspan="6">(2) Total grants include grants of Asylum, Humanitarian Protection, Discretionary Leave, grants under family and private life rules, Leave Outside the Rules and UASC leave</td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p><br></p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2015-11-12T16:03:10.647Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425250/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425250/answer","Number of Iraqi nationals granted asylum or another form of protection.xlsx","Number of Iraqi nationals granted asylum or another form of protection.xlsx","Number of Iraqi nationals","Number of Iraqi nationals","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425250/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-11-02","Refugees: Iraq","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Bates on 22 October (HL2920), how many Iraqis have been granted refugee status in the United Kingdom in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Lord Green of Deddington",,"Lord Green of Deddington","HL3176"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425251","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-16","<p>The government is committed to tackling the fraudulent evasion of duty. HM Revenue &amp; Customs (HMRC) records statistics for excise offences in Northern Ireland by regime; hydrocarbon oil, tobacco and alcohol. It does not separate out those involving smuggling between the Republic of Ireland and the United Kingdom.</p><br /><p>By their very nature these offences can include cross border aspects and HMRC works closely with the Revenue Commissioners in the Republic of Ireland to disrupt criminal activity connected with these goods. This includes regular exchange of intelligence, joint operational activity and the gathering of evidence for use in criminal prosecutions.</p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2015-11-16T16:11:19.46Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425251/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425251/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425251/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-02","Smuggling: Northern Ireland","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the extent of cross-border smuggling between Northern Ireland and the Republic of Ireland, and how many prosecutions for such smuggling have been recorded in the past five years.","false","Biography information for Baroness Harris of Richmond",,"Baroness Harris of Richmond","HL3177"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425252","Department for International Development","false","2015-11-18","<p>The UK values the European Union’s long-standing relationship with the African, Caribbean and Pacific (ACP) group of states, as currently governed by the Cotonou Partnership Agreement (CPA), which is due to expire in February 2020. The European Union (EU) and its Member States are in the early stages of considering the content and structure of this relationship after 2020. It will need to be rooted in the Agenda 2030 on Sustainable Development, including considering how to move beyond mainly aid implementation.</p><br /><p>The EU has recently launched a public consultation to explore this, aiming to take stock of the CPA’s performance and understand how the EU-ACP relationship could be improved in the future. The UK welcomes the public consultation, which can be found is attached for your convenience.</p><br /> <br />",,"Baroness Verma",,"2015-11-18T16:23:40.423Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425252/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425252/answer","joint-consultation-paper-post-cotonou_en_0.pdf","joint-consultation-paper-post-cotonou_en_0.pdf","EU's joint consultation paper","EU's joint consultation paper","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425252/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-11-02","ACP Countries: EU External Relations","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their assessment of the prospects for future relations between the African, Caribbean and Pacific group of states and the European Union.","false","Biography information for Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead",,"Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead","HL3178"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425253","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-16","<p>We recognise the important work of the UN Commission of Inquiry and are concerned by their findings on human rights in Eritrea, in particular reports of arbitrary detention, and shortcomings in the rule of law and respect for fundamental freedoms. At the Human Rights Council in July, we supported an extension of the Commission’s mandate so that it can continue its work.</p><p>We regret that the Commission has been unable to visit Eritrea and therefore had to rely on witnesses who are outside of Eritrea and whose testimony may have been based on first-hand experience of Eritrea some time ago. We have made clear to the Government of Eritrea that it must improve respect for human rights and honour its international obligations, including allowing the Commission access.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-11-16T14:08:28.483Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425253/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425253/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425253/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-11-02","Eritrea: Human Rights","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their assessment of the recent UN Commission of Inquiry report on human rights abuses in Eritrea under President Isaias Afwerki.","false","Biography information for Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead",,"Baroness Kinnock of Holyhead","HL3179"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425254","Department for Education","false","2015-11-10","<p>The judgment suggests there is an existing legal remedy for claims of caste-associated discrimination, under the ‘ethnic origins’ element of Section 9 of the Equality Act 2010.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2015-11-10T16:19:06.407Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425254/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425254/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425254/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-11-02","Castes: Discrimination","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the answer by Baroness Williams of Trafford on 15 July (HL Deb, col 575), whether they will clarify how the judgment in <i>Tirkey v Chandhok</i> has changed the law on caste discrimination.","false","Biography information for Lord Lester of Herne Hill",,"Lord Lester of Herne Hill","HL3180"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425255","Department for Education","false","2015-11-12","<p>We are currently considering the need for a consultation on caste discrimination. This is part of our wider consideration of the implications of the Tirkey v Chandok tribunal judgments.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2015-11-12T15:51:29.263Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425255/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425255/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425255/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-11-02","Castes: Discrimination","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they next plan to consider the case for further consultation on caste discrimination.","false","Biography information for Lord Lester of Herne Hill",,"Lord Lester of Herne Hill","HL3181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425256","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-11-17","<p>As set out in my Written Answer HL2680 on 30 October 2015, under the Human Rights Act 1998 (section 6), all public authorities are under a duty to act in compliance with the Convention rights set out in that Act. As the law on defamation in Northern Ireland is a devolved matter, it is for the Northern Ireland Executive, in considering its policy on the subject, to reach a view on whether the policy under consideration is compatible with the Convention rights.</p>",,"Lord Faulks",,"2015-11-17T12:20:29.36Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425256/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425256/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425256/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-11-02","Defamation: Northern Ireland","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what role the Secretary of State has in ensuring that the law of defamation in Northern Ireland is compatible with the European Convention on Human Rights.","false","Biography information for Lord Lester of Herne Hill",,"Lord Lester of Herne Hill","HL3182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425257","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-11-16","<p>The Lord Chancellor has responsibility for ensuring an effective and efficient system of tribunal administration. This duty encompasses the First-tier Tribunal. The Lord Chancellor must also uphold the continued independence of the judiciary and in doing so have regard to their need to have the support necessary to enable them to exercise their functions.</p><p>HM Courts &amp; Tribunals Service has allocated additional court time in place between December 2015 and June 2016 to ensure current waiting times do not increase for the tribunal user.</p>",,"Lord Faulks",,"2015-11-16T12:57:15.223Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425257/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425257/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425257/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-11-02","Immigration: Appeals","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Faulks on 2 November (HL2703), what duty they have, if any, to enable First Tier Tribunals to deal with asylum and immigration cases fairly and within a reasonable time.","false","Biography information for Lord Lester of Herne Hill",,"Lord Lester of Herne Hill","HL3183"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425258","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-17","<p>Electoral Registration Officers (EROs) in Great Britain already work with their local schools and colleges to identify and register young people.</p><p>In a report before the start of the current canvass of electors in Great Britain, the Electoral Commission called on all EROs to update their local public engagement strategies for the canvass. The Commission noted that strategies should reflect the activity EROs intended to carry out to target under-registered groups, such as attainers.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2015-11-17T16:32:59.81Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425258/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425258/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425258/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-02","Electoral Register: Young People","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they will ensure that local electoral registration offices in England and Wales work closely with schools, as has been done in Northern Ireland, to increase the number of young people registered to vote.","false","Biography information for Lord Lexden",,"Lord Lexden","HL3184"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425259","Department for Education","false","2015-11-16","<p>The Government does not approve the sale of playing fields but assesses applications from schools and local authorities to dispose of them. A disposal can include a lease of the playing fields to a third-party commercial organisation with the fields, following investment and improvement, continuing to be used by the school.</p><p>It is neither the government nor the Department for Education that instigate the disposal of playing fields. It is the local authorities, academies or schools that seek consent to convert these often surplus or un-used fields to enable them to invest in school sport or education. However, there is strict control in place which requires an assessment of the facilities available to pupils. The government will only give permission to dispose of school playing fields if it is clearly demonstrated that they are surplus to requirements and the sports and curriculum needs of the school and its neighbouring schools will continue to be met.</p><p>Since any approved disposal would not impact on the provision of the sports curriculum at the school/s, no follow up studies on the sale of playing fields has been undertaken.</p>",,"Lord Nash",,"2015-11-16T16:36:05.387Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425259/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425259/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425259/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-11-02","Schools: Playing Fields","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the impact of the sale of the playing fields of over 100 schools since 2010 on the physical fitness of young people.","false","Biography information for Lord Lexden",,"Lord Lexden","HL3185"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425260","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-16","<p>Under the voluntary agreement with the National Housing Federation, there will be a presumption that housing association tenants will have the right to purchase their home at Right to Buy level discounts, but associations will not be obliged to sell particular properties where there are reasons why this would not be in the interests of their operations.</p><p>This includes housing associations exercising discretion over the sale of properties provided through charitable or public-benefit resources or bequeathed for charitable or public-benefit purposes, and in the possession of the housing association before it became registered under the Housing Act 1974 (or later equivalent legislation).</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2015-11-16T16:37:35.063Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425260/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425260/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425260/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-11-02","Right to Buy Scheme: Housing Associations","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in implementing the proposed voluntary agreement with housing associations regarding the extended right to buy, how they will safeguard the land interests of charities that have been acquired by charitable donation.","false","Biography information for Lord Patel of Bradford",,"Lord Patel of Bradford","HL3186"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425261","Department of Health","false","2015-11-16","<p>We have not formally reviewed the 2015 Obeid paper but officials are aware of its conclusions which are in line with information already considered by Ministers.</p><p>The recommendation in the Teratology Society in essence repeats current advice on folic acid supplements. There are no plans to review this advice.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL3189","2015-11-16T14:05:51.237Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425261/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425261/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425261/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-02","Neural Tube Defects","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the implications of research published by Obeid <i>et al</i> on preventable spina bifida and anencephaly in Europe for the development of a policy to reduce births affected by neural tube defects.","false","Biography information for Lord Rooker",,"Lord Rooker","HL3187"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425262","Department of Health","false","2015-11-12","<p>The Department has not made an assessment of the lifetime direct medical costs associated with spina bifida, compared to births without spina bifida.</p><br /><p>We are however aware of research from 2011 in the European Journal of Pediatrics which shows the costs to be significant. A copy is attached and can be found at:</p><p><strong></strong></p><p><a href="http://www.researchgate.net/publication/51148532_Economic_burden_of_neural_tube_defects_and_impact_of_prevention_with_folic_acid_A_literature_review" target="_blank">http://www.researchgate.net/publication/51148532_Economic_burden_of_neural_tube_defects_and_impact_of_prevention_with_folic_acid_A_literature_review</a></p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2015-11-12T13:09:03.367Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425262/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425262/answer","European Journal of Pediatrics.pdf","European Journal of Pediatrics.pdf","European Journal of Pediatrics","European Journal of Pediatrics","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425262/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-02","Spina Bifida","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the lifetime direct medical costs associated with spina bifida, compared to births without spina bifida.","false","Biography information for Lord Rooker",,"Lord Rooker","HL3188"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425263","Department of Health","false","2015-11-16","<p>We have not formally reviewed the 2015 Obeid paper but officials are aware of its conclusions which are in line with information already considered by Ministers.</p><p>The recommendation in the Teratology Society in essence repeats current advice on folic acid supplements. There are no plans to review this advice.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL3187","2015-11-16T14:05:51.317Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425263/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425263/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425263/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-02","Folic Acid","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to review the Teratology Society recommendation regarding mandating folic acid fortification in Europe.","false","Biography information for Lord Rooker",,"Lord Rooker","HL3189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425264","Department of Health","false","2015-11-16","<p>Data about fortifying and non-fortifying countries is not extensive and does not identify fortifiers and non-fortifiers in a meaningful way. As a result we do not have comparable data for prevalence of births with neural tube defects (NTDs) across the European Union or with North America pre and post fortification. Available data on prevalence is in the public domain and is listed below:</p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="2"><p>Prevalence of NTD per 10,000 births for those EU members states where figures are available</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>United Kingdom</p></td><td><p>12.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Belgium 8</p></td><td><p>8.54</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Croatia</p></td><td><p>4.64</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Denmark</p></td><td><p>11.24</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>France</p></td><td><p>12.70</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Germany</p></td><td><p>11.00</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Ireland</p></td><td><p>8.19</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Italy</p></td><td><p>5.36</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Netherlands</p></td><td><p>6.71</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Poland</p></td><td><p>10.14</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Portugal</p></td><td><p>4.27</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Spain</p></td><td><p>9.55</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p><em>Source:</em> EUROCAT Special Report: Prevalence of Neural Tube Defects in younger mothers in Europe 20002008. EUROCAT (2010)</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>United States</p></td><td><p>6.5</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p><em>Source:</em> Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC). Updated Estimates of Neural Tube Defects Prevented by Mandatory Folic Acid Fortification — United States, 1995–2011. Morbidity and Mortality Weekly Report. 2015; 64: 1-5.</p><br />",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL3191","2015-11-16T14:05:19.473Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425264/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425264/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425264/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-02","Neural Tube Defects: Folic Acid","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what information they have about the average prevalence of births affected by neural tube defects in countries applying food fortification with folic acid compared to those countries that do not.","false","Biography information for Lord Rooker",,"Lord Rooker","HL3190"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425265","Department of Health","false","2015-11-16","<p>Data about fortifying and non-fortifying countries is not extensive and does not identify fortifiers and non-fortifiers in a meaningful way. As a result we do not have comparable data for prevalence of births with neural tube defects (NTDs) across the European Union or with North America pre and post fortification. Available data on prevalence is in the public domain and is listed below:</p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="2"><p>Prevalence of NTD per 10,000 births for those EU members states where figures are available</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>United Kingdom</p></td><td><p>12.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Belgium 8</p></td><td><p>8.54</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Croatia</p></td><td><p>4.64</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Denmark</p></td><td><p>11.24</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>France</p></td><td><p>12.70</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Germany</p></td><td><p>11.00</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Ireland</p></td><td><p>8.19</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Italy</p></td><td><p>5.36</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Netherlands</p></td><td><p>6.71</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Poland</p></td><td><p>10.14</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Portugal</p></td><td><p>4.27</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Spain</p></td><td><p>9.55</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p><em>Source:</em> EUROCAT Special Report: Prevalence of Neural Tube Defects in younger mothers in Europe 20002008. EUROCAT (2010)</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>United States</p></td><td><p>6.5</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p><em>Source:</em> Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC). Updated Estimates of Neural Tube Defects Prevented by Mandatory Folic Acid Fortification — United States, 1995–2011. Morbidity and Mortality Weekly Report. 2015; 64: 1-5.</p><br />",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","HL3190","2015-11-16T14:05:19.41Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425265/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/425265/answer",,,,,"http:/